{In this game, Sjugirov demonstrates the right move order. The first 10 moves
repeat his game with Sakaev.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. a3 Bb7 5. Nc3 Ne4
6. Nxe4 Bxe4 7. Bf4 d6 8. e3 Nd7 9. Bd3 Bb7 10. e4 e5 $1 {This is the correct
decision. Now, White cannot go for a KID type of structure by means of d4-d5.}
11. dxe5 $2 {This is a typical tactical mistake that you should know.} ({
Of course, White should have played} 11. Be3 {With the bishop still on f8,
however, Black can opt for} exd4 12. Nxd4 g6 13. Qd2 Bg7 {It's clear that the
bishop is more active on g7 than on e7. A possible follow up would be} 14. O-O
O-O 15. f3 a5 $132 {with ...Nc5 to follow. Black is doing fine.}) 11... dxe5
12. Nxe5 $2 {Now, this move is already losing. Contrary to the previous
example, here the moves 0-0 and ...Be7 are not included.} ({After} 12. Bxe5 $6
Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Qd4 $17 14. Nf3 Qxb2 15. Qa4+ c6 16. O-O O-O-O $17 {Black has a
huge advantage.}) ({More tenacious would have been} 12. Be3 {when Black will
play} Bc5 {with the idea to execute the strategically desirable exchange of
the dark-squared bishops. After such an exchange, Black would enjoy an obvious
advantage due to his superior bishop and the weak d4-square.}) 12... Bd6 $1 {
Once again, this is the point! It turns out that White is losing on the spot.}
13. Nxf7 {This is already desperation.} ({Now, the pin} 13. Qa4 {does not work
as in the previous example because White's king is still in the centre. Black
should play} Bxe5 14. Bxe5 O-O 15. Bd4 Ne5 16. Bxe5 Qxd3 $19 {with a
completely winning position.}) ({The attempt to protect the knight with} 13.
Qh5 {is well met by} Nxe5 14. Bxe5 g6 $19 {when White is dropping the bishop.})
13... Kxf7 14. Bxd6 cxd6 $19 {White does not have any compensation for the
piece. Black is winning.} 15. O-O Qf6 16. b4 Rhf8 17. c5 dxc5 18. Bc4+ Ke7 19.
Qe2 Rae8 20. Rad1 Ne5 21. Bb5 Rd8 22. bxc5 bxc5 23. Qe3 Rd4 24. f3 Rfd8 25. Rc1
c4 26. f4 Ng4 27. Qg3 h5 28. e5 Qb6 29. Qh4+ Kf8 30. Qxh5 Rd1+ 31. Kh1 Nf2+ 32.
Kg1 Nh3+ 33. Kh1 Qg1+ 34. Rxg1 Nf2# 0-1

