{In this example, we shall see what could happen if White combines Ne5 with
the immediate Qf3.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 b6 3. Nc3 Bb7 4. Nf3 e6 5. e3 d5 6. cxd5
exd5 7. Bb5+ c6 8. Bd3 Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Ne5 c5 11. Qf3 {[%cal Gf1d1] Besides
trying to quickly transfer the queen to h3, White is planning to cover the
d4-pawn by means of Rd1. The drawback of this move is that the e5-knight
temporarily lacks protection. Black played the most principled} Nc6 12. Rd1 {
This is the point.} ({In case of} 12. Qh3 {the simplest would be} h6 {[%cal
Gf8e8,Ge7d6] planning to proceed with ...Re8 followed by ...Bd6.}) 12... Bd6 $1
{Once again, Black plays the most precise move. He is using the fact that
White is not in time to support the knight by means of f2-f4.} 13. Ng4 {
By deflecting the f6-knight, White is trying to weaken the d5-pawn. Black,
however, has enough time to stabilize the position -} Nxg4 14. Qxg4 c4 $1 {
Gaining space on the queenside and making the d1-rook useless. Before going
for this thematic advance, you have to make sure that White cannot execute the
advance e3-e4 in a favourable way.} 15. Bf1 Ne7 {[%cal Gf7f5] This move comes
just in time. Black covers the d5-pawn and is ready to follow with ...f7-f5.}
16. g3 $6 {This passive move only increases Black's advantage.} ({Given the
fact that Black is statically better, White should have looked for dynamic
counterplay. In this direction, a logical try would have been} 16. b3 a6 17.
bxc4 dxc4 18. e4 b5 {Even though the position remains very complicated,
Black's play is easier from a practical point of view. White has nothing
concrete in the centre and on the kingside while ...b5-b4 followed by ...c4-c3
is already on the agenda.}) 16... f5 17. Qh3 a6 {[%cal Gb6b5] Since White does
not have any counterplay, Black can already start preparing his queenside
expansion.} 18. a4 Qd7 {[%cal Gb6b5,Gb5b4] All the preparation are done. The
advance ...b6-b5-b4 is coming. Therefore, White tried to create counterplay by
means of} 19. e4 dxe4 20. Bxc4+ Kh8 21. Bg5 Ng6 $17 {Black has a space
advantage, better structure, and more active pieces. His advantage is beyond
any doubt. Later on, he managed to win the game.} 22. Bb3 Rae8 23. Ne2 Bb8 24.
Rac1 Bd5 25. Bxd5 Qxd5 26. Nc3 Qb3 27. Qf1 f4 28. Qxa6 h6 29. Bxf4 Bxf4 30.
gxf4 Nxf4 31. Rd2 Qe6 0-1

